def dist_box_violin(data):
 # function plots a combined graph for univariate analysis of continous variable 
 #to check spread, central tendency , dispersion and outliers  
    Name=data.name.upper()
    fig, axes =plt.subplots(1,3,figsize=(17, 7))
    fig.suptitle("SPREAD OF DATA FOR "+ Name  , fontsize=18, fontweight='bold')
    sns.distplot(data,kde=False,color='Blue',ax=axes[0])
    axes[0].axvline(data.mean(), color='y', linestyle='--',linewidth=2)
    axes[0].axvline(data.median(), color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)
    axes[0].axvline(data.mode()[0],color='g',linestyle='solid',linewidth=2)
    axes[0].legend({'Mean':data.mean(),'Median':data.median(),'Mode':data.mode()})
    sns.boxplot(x=data,showmeans=True, orient='h',color="purple",ax=axes[1])
    #just exploring violin plot
    sns.violinplot(data,ax=axes[2],showmeans=True)

# Function to create barplots that indicate percentage for each category.
def bar_perc(plot, feature):
    '''
    plot
    feature: 1-d categorical feature array
    '''
    total = len(feature) # length of the column
    for p in plot.patches:
        percentage = '{:.1f}%'.format(100 * p.get_height()/total) # percentage of each class of the category
        x = p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2 - 0.05 # width of the plot
        y = p.get_y() + p.get_height()           # hieght of the plot
        plot.annotate(percentage, (x, y), size = 12) # annotate the percentage

CONCLUSIONS:¶

  1. 44.4% customers brought TM195. TM195 model is the most purchased model. TM498 was purchased more than TM798.
  2. Most of the male customers, 57.8% bought TM498.
  3. Partenered customers were 59%.
  4. Median is 181 and the average education is 16.
  5. Younger customers are buying the treadmill with an average age of customer being 26 and mode is 25.
  6. Most of the customers are in lower pay range and earn less than 70K.
  7. Males average usage is more than the average usage of females.

CUSTOMER PROFILES OF MODELS¶

A) TM195

  1. TM195 is the most popular model with customer access rate of more than 40 % approximately.
  2. Customer belief is the more valuable when TM195 is used, and might be looking for a basic treadmill doing the job.
  3. Most customers who bought this treadmill are partenered Females and males compared to single ones.
  4. Customers buying this treadmill has an income less than 60000 with a median of 55000.

B) TM498

  1. TM498 is sold more than TM798 hence proving to be the most popular.
  2. Average Income of the customer is 48,973.
  3. Customers with lower income purchase TM195 and TM498 model may be because of cost of the Treadmill
  4. Average age of customer who purchases TM498 is 28.9 , Median is 26 . Customer range is between 24-33.
  5. Bachelor's average year is 16 who bought this treadmill.

c) TM798

  1. Average age of customer who purchases TM798 is 29 , Median is 27 . Seeing that there are more outliers, customers must be attracted mostly who are above the age of 40.
  2. Average education age is 17 years.
  3. Expected usage is 4-5 day a week
  4. Expected Miles to run is on an Average 166 miles per week and median is 160.
  5. Average Income is 75K and median is 76K

RECOMMENDATIONS:¶

  1. Seeing the cost of the treadmill models TM498 is best suited to be rated the good treadmill.
  2. Customers to be dealt with promotional and discount prices for more sales.
  3. Branding of all the treadmills to be done, mostly the TM798 being as a high class treadmill.
  4. Create promotional advirtisements to lure the customers hence increasing sales.
